The paper proposes a new approach to clustering using a recurrent model that learns how to cluster. This falls under the domain of machine learning, specifically in the sub-field of deep learning. The paper also mentions the use of synthetic and real datasets, which suggests a focus on data-driven approaches. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
